      "content": "i was just looking at some stuff about the heat death of the universe and it just hit me... like, if everything eventually just reaches total equilibrium and every trace of us is gone forever, then what is the actual point of any of this? all the struggle, all the pain, all the effort... it feels like we're just playing a game that's already been decided is a loss. does anything actually matter if it's all just destined to be nothing?",
